hadoop fs <args>


HDFS and MapRFS commands•  
hadoop fs –mkdir mydir – is used to make a new directory• 
hadoop fs –copyFromLocal /etc/ho sts mydir – will copy a file from your local file system into the mapr-FS• 
hadoop fs –lsr mydir – will recursiv ely list the directory contents•
hadoop fs –cat mydir/hosts – will display the contents of a file•
hadoop fs –rm mydir/h – will remove the specified fileMapR FS Specific Commands•
hadoop mfs –ln mydir yourdir – will create a link between two directories•
hadoop mfs –setcompression off mydir – will turn off compression for the files of a di rectory• 
hadoop mfs –setchunksize 65536 mydir – sets the chunk size for the files of a directoryStandard POSIX comm ands that work in MapR-FS• 
mkdir to make a directory•
cp to copy a file• 
ls to list the contents of a direc tory•  
ln to create a link between two directories• 
rm to remove a file• 
tail – for copying a selected part of a file• 
grep and awk – for searching inpute for patterns• 
sed – edit streaming files




hadoop fs -ls .
